ussia, Prussia, Germany","Toruń, Kuyavia-Pomerania, Poland":"Toruń, Kuyavia-Pomerania, Poland","Torun, Posen, Preussen, Germany":"Posen, Prussia","Slovakia":"Slovakia","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Slavic","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Slovenian (<b>Slavič</b>) and Croatian (<b>Slavić</b>):","nickname from Slovenian archaic <i>slavič</i> and Croatian <i>slavić</i> ‘nightingale’, probably denoting someone with a good voice.","patronymic from a short form of any of various personal names composed of the Slavic element <i>slav</i> ‘glory’ or ‘famous’ (from <i>slava</i> ‘glory’). Compare   Slavich  ,   Slavick  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Slavich","meanings":["Americanized form of Slovenian <b>Slavič</b> and Croatian <b>Slavić</b> (see   Slavic  )."]}]},{"name":"Gilda","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["apparently of Germanic origin, representing a feminine short form of names containing the element <i>gild</i> ‘sacrifice’ (  compare e.g.  Hermengildo   ). Its occasional use in the English-speaking world since the 19th century may have been prompted by the character in  Verdi's  Rigoletto, the innocent daughter of the hunchback jester  Rigoletto , who becomes the object of the Duke of Mantua's affections and is murdered on her father's orders as the result of a series of misunderstandings."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1352627,"age":20,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"description":"The Jagiellonian Dynasty.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Gilda Slavic was born on 13 July 1361, in Slovakia. She married Stefan Torun in 1380, in Toruń, Kuyavia-Pomerania, Poland. They were the parents of at least 3 sons and 1 daughter. She died on 15 October 1390, in Thorn, Thorn, West Prussia, Prussia, Germany, at the age of 29, and was buried in Toruń, Poland."},"et":{"13 July 1361–15 October 1390":"13. juuli 1361